    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Materials</strong> : You require 50 gp worth of rare chalks and inks.</p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong> </p><ul><li><p>You draw a 10-foot diameter circle on the ground, inscribed with sigils, creating a portal.</p></li><li><p>The teleportation circle must link to a permanent teleportation circle, whose sigil sequence you know, and is on the same plane of existence as you.</p></li><li><p>After the circle is complete, the portal remains open until the end of your next turn.</p></li><li><p>Any creature that enters the portal instantly appears within 5 feet of the destination circle, or the nearest unoccupied space.</p></li><li><p>You can create a permanent teleportation circle by casting this spell in the same location every day for one year.</p></li></ul><p><em>Many major temples, guilds, and other important places have permanent teleportation circles inscribed somewhere within their confines. Each such circle includes a unique sigil sequenceâ€”a string of magical runes arranged in a particular pattern. When you first gain the ability to cast this spell, you learn the sigil sequences for two destinations on the Material Plane, determined by the DM. You can learn additional sigil sequences during your adventures. You can commit a new sigil sequence to memory after studying it for 1 minute.</em></p>",
